se xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526169\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526169\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bpd1665702947825.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bpd1665702947825.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bpd1665702947825.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bpd1665702947825\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Database Access on Microsoft SQL Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can access the database by configuring the logon path in the assignment file or when using the ProcScript <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> command.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__section_w1478ab1b5b1_w1479ab1b5_w1480ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__section_w1481ab1b5b3_w1482ab1b5_w1483ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d235866e59\">\n                        \n Logon Information\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52697e1_d52698e1_d52699e1\">In the assignment file, specify the driver and database path:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVERS]\nMSS = <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>\n[PATHS]\n$MSS MSS:<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSourceName</var>:{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>}|{<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>}|{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24755e1_d24756e1_d24757e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>—connector version identifier, for example U5.2.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24758e1_d24759e1_d24760e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSourceName</var>—configured ODBC data source name.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24761e1_d24762e1_d24763e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>—database name; optional if a default database is specified in the ODBC DSN (Data Source Name).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24764e1_d24765e1_d24766e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>—user and password as configured in the ODBC data source; optional—can be left empty if integrated security is used.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52700e1_d52701e1_d52702e1\">From ProcScript, you can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> statement:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">open \"<var class=\"keyword varname\">DataSourceName</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database|User|Password</var>\",\"MSS\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__section_w1484ab1b5b5_w1485ab1b5_w1486ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d235866e132\">\n                        \n Using MS-SQL as the Repository\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52724e1_d52725e1_d52726e1\">Microsoft SQL Server can be used for the Uniface Repository. To do so:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24779e1_d24780e1_d24781e1\">Generate a SQL script from the command line using\n               the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gensql /meta</span> switch for the Microsoft SQL Server. For more\n               information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cck1665702542032.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cck1665702542032.html\" title=\"The /genSql switch generates DBMS-specific SQL command scripts for preparing an application database or the Uniface Repository, including creating tables and enforcing referential integrity constraints in the database.\">/genSql</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24782e1_d24783e1_d24784e1\">Edit the script before running it by adding a suitable <code class=\"ph codeph\">use database</code> statement. Run the script from a SQL Workbench, for example, the Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio, to create the Repository tables and indexes. Note: The script generated by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gensql</span> switch does not contain definitions for triggers and stored procedures.\n                          </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__li_d24785e1_d24786e1_d24787e1\">In the <span class=\"ph filepath\">dbms.asn</span> file located in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/adm</span> directory, modify the $IDF path to point to the MSS logon path. For example:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$DBMS $MSS</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__section_w1487ab1b5b7_w1488ab1b5_w1489ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d235866e181\">\n                        Open/Close Support</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52730e1_d52731e1_d52732e1\">Both the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> and\n\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> ProcScript instructions are fully supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52733e1_d52734e1_d52735e1\">For example, if a default database has been defined for data source ROSE, you can specify the ProcScript statement <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> as follows, where as is the user name and db the password:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">open \"ROSE:|sa|dba\",\"mss\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52736e1_d52737e1_d52738e1\">Integrated security is assumed if you do not supply a user and password in the assignment file or the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> ProcScript statement. For example, to log onto data source ROSE, database <var class=\"keyword varname\">test</var> with integrated security, you must specify the ProcScript statement <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">open \"ROSE:test||\",\"mss\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__section_w1490ab1b5b9_w1491ab1b5_w1492ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d235866e221\">\n                        \n Loss of Connection\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bpd1665702947825__p_d52742e1_d52743e1_d52744e1\">If the SQLState is 08S01 (Communication link failure), indicating that the connection with the database has been lost, the MSS connector returns <code class=\"ph codeph\">-9</code> in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526169\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526169\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Access on Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Access on Microsoft SQL Server You can access the database by configuring the logon path in the assignment file or when using the ProcScript open command. Logon Information In the assignment file, specify the driver and database path: [DRIVERS] MSS = Version [PATHS] $MSS MSS: DataSourceName :{ Database }|{ User }|{ Password } Copy Version —connector version identifier, for example U5.2. DataSourceName —configured ODBC data source name. Database —database name; optional if a default database is specified in the ODBC DSN (Data Source Name). User and Password —user and password as configured in the ODBC data source; optional—can be left empty if integrated security is used. From ProcScript, you can use the open statement: open \" DataSourceName : Database|User|Password \",\"MSS\" Copy Using MS-SQL as the Repository Microsoft SQL Server can be used for the Uniface Repository. To do so: Generate a SQL script from the command line using the /gensql /meta switch for the Microsoft SQL Server. For more information, see /genSql . Edit the script before running it by adding a suitable use database statement. Run the script from a SQL Workbench, for example, the Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio, to create the Repository tables and indexes. Note: The script generated by the /gensql switch does not contain definitions for triggers and stored procedures. In the dbms.asn file located in the /common/adm directory, modify the $IDF path to point to the MSS logon path. For example: [PATHS] $DBMS $MSS Copy Open/Close Support Both the open and close ProcScript instructions are fully supported. For example, if a default database has been defined for data source ROSE, you can specify the ProcScript statement open as follows, where as is the user name and db the password: open \"ROSE:|sa|dba\",\"mss\" Copy Integrated security is assumed if you do not supply a user and password in the assignment file or the open ProcScript statement. For example, to log onto data source ROSE, database test with integrated security, you must specify the ProcScript statement open as follows: open \"ROSE:test||\",\"mss\" Copy Loss of Connection If the SQLState is 08S01 (Communication link failure), indicating that the connection with the database has been lost, the MSS connector returns -9 in $procerror or $status . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}